com.pb.sawdust.io

Interface RuntimeCloseable

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.AutoCloseable, java.io.Closeable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    IterableReader<D>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AsciiTableWriter, CsvTableWriter, DelimitedTextTableWriter, IterableFileReader.LineIterableReader, TextTableWriter

    public interface RuntimeCloseable
extends java.io.Closeable
    The RuntimeCloseable interface is essentially a replica of the java.io.Closeable interface, with the checked exceptions removed.

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void close()
      Closes this stream and releases any system resources associated with it.

    • Method Detail

      • close

        void close()
        Closes this stream and releases any system resources associated with it. If the stream is already closed then invoking this method has no effect. This is identical to the method prescribed in java.io.Closeable, except it has no checked exception.
        Specified by:
        close in interface java.lang.AutoCloseable
        Specified by:
        close in interface java.io.Closeable
